{
  "quest.4A1F5EA13AF49DDA.quest_subtitle": "Turn loot back into ingredients",
  "task.31EC56B4B7D51F67.title": "Craft an Uncrafting Table",
  "quest.4137D6CD3FC01F40.quest_desc": [
    "Gather wood from your random blocks and craft a crafting table.",
    "",
    "The quest completes when a crafting table is in your inventory.",
  ],
  "task.1F223341E102CF8B.title": "Read about Good to Know Mods",
  "quest.4137D6CD3FC01F40.quest_subtitle": "Your first workbench",
  "quest.2B9686474CA8C9C3.title": "Random Pools",
  "quest.2B9686474CA8C9C3.quest_subtitle": "Why your loot changes over time",
  "quest.2B9686474CA8C9C3.quest_desc": [
    "Every time you mine the center block on your island, it is replaced by a random block from your team's &6effective pool&r — not every block in the entire modpack at once.",
    "",
    "&eAt the start&r, that pool is intentionally small: mostly &avanilla Minecraft&r blocks, plus a few starter mods (custom compression blocks, the Uncrafting Table mod, and OpenBlocks Elevator). That makes early rolls easier to use — wood, dirt, cobble, ores, and basic building blocks show up far more often than complex machines.",
    "",
    "As you progress through the quest book and unlock other mods, those mod's blocks are &aadded to your pool&r. Completing certain quests (for example storage chapters) can automatically enable a whole mod namespace for your team. The more you unlock, the wider the loot table becomes — expect rarer vanilla results and more modded blocks, machines, and decor as you advance.",
    "",
    "This is by design: early skyblock is about simple materials and crafting; later game brings the full pack. Keep mining the same center block — the pool grows with you, you do not need a new generator.",
    "",
    "Tip: later chapters explain specific unlocks. Operators can inspect the pool with &f/randomblock pools list&r.",
  ],
  "task.68102B3B6DBD2C07.title": "cant mine the block in front of you.. remove it with this chapter reward",
  "quest.6639B6CEC400B59F.title": "Good To Know",
  "quest.51521D28751E05D4.title": "Flying Items",
  "quest.4137D6CD3FC01F40.title": "Craft a Crafting Table",
  "task.7B73F034EBE58ADA.title": "Read about flying items",
  "quest.7A5DE9240428A708.title": "Cant mine the block?",
  "quest.6639B6CEC400B59F.quest_desc": [
    "The Good to Know Mods chapter introduces key mods in this pack. Each quest is a quick read — and many hand out rewards that can help you early.",
    "",
    "Open the Good to Know Mods tab in your quest book and complete the checkmark quests. Gateways, Sophisticated Storage, and more are explained there with free items waiting when you finish.",
  ],
  "task.42B5325C25528463.title": "Random Pools",
  "quest.54426B5BBE263DB4.title": "Welcome to Randon One Block",
  "task.1A4C7E9B0D2F3865.title": "Read the welcome message",
  "task.33E107AC2A3D7A05.title": "Obtain a Crafting Table",
  "quest.4A1F5EA13AF49DDA.quest_desc": [
    "Your random block spits out all kinds of crafted blocks — stairs, slabs, doors, machines, and more. The Uncrafting Table reverses normal crafting recipes so you can recover the ingredients.",
    "",
    "This is one of the most important blocks in the pack. Mine something you cannot place or do not need, drop it in the Uncrafting Table, and get wood, ingots, and other mats back instead of stuffing your chests with dead loot.",
    "",
    "The Uncrafting Table can also spawn from your random block — keep mining and you might get one before you craft it.",
    "",
    "Craft one early and keep it next to your crafting table.",
  ],
  "quest.4A1F5EA13AF49DDA.title": "Uncrafting Table",
  "quest.4C45A23F18643143.title": "Crafting Table on a Stick",
  "quest.4C45A23F18643143.quest_subtitle": "Craft anywhere on your island",
  "quest.4C45A23F18643143.quest_desc": [
    "Skyblock means you are always one block away from the void. The &eCrafting on a Stick&r mod lets you carry a workbench in your inventory instead of placing one down every time you need to craft.",
    "",
    "Craft a &6Crafting Table on a Stick&r (same recipe shape as a normal crafting table, using the mod's item). Hold it, use it like a tool, and open a full 3×3 crafting grid on the spot — perfect while you are mining the center block, sorting random loot, or working at the edge of your platform.",
    "",
    "Pair it with your normal crafting table at base: keep the stick for field crafting and the placed table for bigger projects. It saves space and stops you from losing crafting access when inventory is full of odd blocks from the random pool.",
  ],
  "task.26A14924618FB8F1.title": "Craft a Crafting Table on a Stick",
  "quest.51521D28751E05D4.quest_desc": [
    "Gather items fast and build out your platform. Creative Controllers and Netherite Furnaces from your random block are huge wins — loot can easily fall off the island before you pick it up.",
    "",
    "Expand your island early so items have somewhere to land. Smelt on-site with furnaces and stash bulk resources in storage as soon as you can.",
  ],
}